Three police officers who were arrested for allegedly aiding the escape of self-confessed serial killer Masten Wanjala have been freed on bail. A Nairobi court ruled that the three be freed on a Ksh. 100,000 cash bail pending investigations. Further, the Court ordered that they provide one contact person besides reporting to the investigating officer daily for the next 7 days. Police Inspector Philip Mbithi and Police Constables Boniface Mutuma and Precious Mwende all of Jogoo Police Station were arrested by their colleagues from the Nairobi Regional Criminal Investigations Office. Meanwhile, Wanjala who escaped from police custody on October 13 was beaten to death by a mob at the Mukhweya village, Bungoma on Friday. he area chief Boniface Ndiera confirmed the incident saying he had received a phone call from one of the residents who claimed that Wanjala had been spotted. “Kuna watoto walikuwa wanaenda shule walimuona na wakamtambua na wakakimbia kwa polisi,” Mr Ndiera told Citizen Digital. On realising that his cover had been blown, Wanjala reportedly took to his heels, with scores of local residents hot at his wake. According to reports, he then dashed into a neighbour’s home and locked himself inside as a mob that was baying for his blood gathered. “Wananchi waliokuwa na hamaki walivunja mlango na wakamtoa nje and within two seconds.. walikuwa wamemuua tayari,” the area chief added. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam